The following code should drop the queue_build_Key table in postgresql but for some odd reason the table doesn't get dropped.
{code}                statement.execute("DROP TABLE QUEUE_BUILD_KEY");
{code}

The Bamboo 2.0 instance starts up and when user tries to delete a queue bamboo throws a constraint violation.

The work around for this is to run the "DROP TABLE QUEUE_BUILD_KEY" manually

Hi,

I'm unable to add a comment to a JIRA issue from a bamboo plugin (http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CODEGEIST/BuildBug) because the RemoteComment class bundled in bamboo does not match the RemoteComment defined in the wsdl.

Abridged RemoteComment.java:
{code}
package com.atlassian.jirasoapclient;
/**
 * RemoteComment.java
 *
